# Create_OSX_Build
Create Vanila or Custom dmg

//The below is a vanilla image 
1) Download the latest version OSX
2) Install the OSX on the laptop/ machine you which you created the image.dmg
3) Download the latest version of AutoDMG [https://github.com/MagerValp/AutoDMG/releases]
4) Open text pad and create a the MySite.adtmpl file [Uploaded in the project - for easiness save it in /Applications]
5) Open Terminal and run the following
        /Applications/AutoDMG.app/Contents/MacOS/AutoDMG update
        /Applications/AutoDMG.app/Contents/MacOS/AutoDMG download 10.13.3 17D47 (Note* if the downloaded OSX is a newer version it will stop and show you the new version in terminal)
        /Applications/AutoDMG.app/Contents/MacOS/AutoDMG \build --download-updates --installer /Applications/Install\ macOS\ High\ Sierra.app /Applications/MySite.adtmpl 



//To do a custom build again for easiness ensure all the applications are moved/ located in /Application 
//For example my custom build is (installing - slack, chrome, office products, zoom, McAfee)

1) Download the latest version OSX
2) Install the OSX on the laptop/ machine you which you created the image.dmg
3) Download the latest version of AutoDMG [https://github.com/MagerValp/AutoDMG/releases]
4) Open text pad and create a the MySite.adtmpl file [Uploaded in the project - for easiness save it in /Applications]
5) Open Terminal and run the following
        /Applications/AutoDMG.app/Contents/MacOS/AutoDMG update
        /Applications/AutoDMG.app/Contents/MacOS/AutoDMG download 10.13.3 17D47 (Note* if the downloaded OSX is a newer version it will stop and show you the new version in terminal)
        /Applications/AutoDMG.app/Contents/MacOS/AutoDMG \build --download-updates --installer /Applications/Install\ macOS\ High\ Sierra.app /Applications/MySite.adtmpl /Applications/Slack.app /Applications/Google\ Chrome.app /Applications/McAfeeSmartInstall.app /Applications/zoom.us.app /Applications/Microsoft\ Excel.app /Applications/Microsoft\ OneNote.app /Applications/Microsoft\ PowerPoint.app /Applications/Microsoft\ Word.app

